TEXT(beginproblem());

$a =  random(11,20,1);
$b = random(27,33,1);
$c = random(45,52,1);
$ans1 = ($c-$b)/$a*100;

Context("Interval");
Context()->flags->set(ignoreEndpointTypes => 1);
Context()->flags->set(tolType=>absolute);
Context()->flags->set(tolerance=>0.5);


###################################


BEGIN_PGML
A car rental company offers the following two plans for renting a car.

    Plan A: [`\$[$b]`] per day and [`[$a]`] cents per mile

    Plan B: [`\$[$c]`] per day with free unlimited mileage

How many miles must one drive in order to justify choosing Plan B?

    One must drive more than [_____]{Real($ans1)} miles to justify choosing Plan B. In other words, it's more economical to use plan B if your number of miles driven will be in the interval [__________]{Interval("($ans1,inf)")}. [@KeyboardInstructions('(Answer using interval notation.)')@]* 

